        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Maybe I"m going against the general consensus here but I have never nor will I ever consider this to be a "must have" necro item.</P><P>Hell, I don't even consider it a very good necro item.</P><P>The manaless fear is nice but I have no problem staying at just about FM when I'm fear kiting so obviously the mana cost of fear isn't hurting me very much. And plus this being a right clickable item the cast time is going to be much longer (I think 7 seconds.) So you would *have* to keep your regular fear up while fear kiting in case something bad went wrong. Seven second fear will get you killed if you put much faith in it. </P><P>I think the item is 6int and 40 mana.. not horrible I suppose but it's 2hb, so no secondary item, this is horrible to be getting only 6 int and 40 mana out of both your primary and secondary slots if bad, plain and simple.</P><P>This doesn't even save a spell gem. I've never even considered buying or camping one.</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Descartes on 07/04/2002  22:17:13<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
