        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         At 6k you got a good deal.<BR>As evidenced by VI's nerfing the drop rate to approximately ZERO, even VI agrees that this thing is pretty powerful.</P><P>&gt;What the hell are you hunting that it takes 4 fears on 1 mob? Not counting resists.</P><P>Generally in Skyfire I use it to chain fear.  At 6 seconds per cast it is just as fast as casting the spell (3 second cast, 3 second reset) after the first one.  And a fight with an Elder Wurm / Elder Wyvern will easily last 30+ seconds ... 5 hits with the fear stick.  At 51 I was still chasing yellows in SF with this thing.</P><P>Heck, I have used this thing to bring down Cazel (not solo, but with another Necro)  When you absolutely need to keep something feared, this stick is great.</P><P>And most of the time I use it without memming Invoke Fear, so it does free up a spell gem.  The only time casting the spell is faster is on the first cast, after that you have to tack on refresh time (so it is about the same.)</P><P><BR>Glonoin on the Rathe</P><P>PS - before I actually had one and spent some time with it, I thought it sucked too.  2HB 6Int 40Mana seems like crap stats, although it looks (graphics) pretty cool, IMHO.  Having spent some quality time with it changed my mind.  It is pretty great and mine isn't for sale ( nor is my pre-nerf circlet :p )</P><P><BR>Using your dead bodies to create a better tomorrow..<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
